---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Haier Appliance Repair | Southern California | 24\" Compact, Urban";
const description = "Haier appliance repair across SoCal. 24\" compact built-ins for urban apartments + ADUs. GE Appliances parent (since 2016). BHGS #A49573. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/haier/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Haier the same as GE Appliances since the 2016 acquisition?",
    a: "Same corporate parent (Haier Group), <b>distinct US product lines</b>, this is the single most important Haier fact to know for service. Haier Group acquired GE Appliances in 2016 and both brands continue operating with separate product lineups, separate US marketing, and separate service channels. <b>GE Appliances</b> (Louisville KY) continues making full-size mainstream US appliances, 30\" ranges, 30-36\" refrigerators, full-size laundry, under the GE / GE Profile / GE Café / GE Monogram brand structure. <b>Haier</b> (as a US-sold brand) focuses <b>compact 24\" appliances for urban apartments</b>, 24\" built-in ovens, 24\" ranges, 24\" refrigerators, 24\" dishwashers, compact laundry. The two are not interchangeable despite shared parent. If you have a Haier oven, parts come through Haier US distribution (separate warehouse from GE Appliances Louisville). If you have a GE oven, see our <a href='/brands/ge-oven-repair/'>GE oven repair</a> page for the full-size US product."
  },
  {
    q: "Why is Haier in LA mostly in apartments and lofts?",
    a: "Haier's US product strategy targets <b>kitchen footprints that don't accommodate full-size 30\" US appliances</b>. 24\" compact built-in ovens fit DTLA loft kitchens, WeHo high-rise condos, Koreatown 1930s apartment buildings, Hollywood hills-side small kitchens, Beverly Hills guest-house kitchens, and Santa Monica beach-town bungalows where the standard 30\" US appliance cutout was never built into the cabinetry. Haier fills the same market slot Magic Chef does in multi-family rental, compact-fit specialization, but with slightly higher-tier positioning, Wi-Fi connectivity (Haier Smart Home app), and better finishes. Most LA Haier owners bought the brand specifically because their kitchen wouldn't fit GE/Samsung/LG mainstream products. Our service concentrates in exactly those neighborhoods."
  },
  {
    q: "Haier Smart Home app vs GE SmartHQ app, which one is my oven?",
    a: "Haier-branded US appliances use the <b>Haier Smart Home app</b> for Wi-Fi pairing + control, a distinct app ecosystem from GE Appliances' <b>SmartHQ app</b> despite shared Haier Group ownership. Don't try to pair a Haier oven with SmartHQ; it won't find the device. Don't try to pair a GE oven with Haier Smart Home; same issue. Haier Smart Home app available on iOS + Android app stores; setup follows standard 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi pairing (router on 2.4 GHz band for initial pairing, most modern routers broadcast both 2.4 + 5 GHz). Common Haier Smart Home pairing issues resolve at 2.4 GHz band check + fresh app install + oven factory reset, same DIY approach as LG SmartThinQ + GE SmartHQ + Samsung SmartThings but through the Haier-specific app. Hardware Wi-Fi module replacement $285-$425 if DIY pairing steps fail."
  },
  {
    q: "Do Haier ovens come in 30\" full size too?",
    a: "In the US market, Haier's product strategy centers on <b>24\" compact</b>. Haier sells full-size appliances in Chinese + global markets but the US product line focuses on the compact-kitchen segment. Exceptions: Haier occasionally sells 30\" appliances in the US market under specific SKU launches (some refrigerator formats, occasional ranges), but 24\" compact is the brand's positioning anchor and where the LA service concentration lives. If you have what you think is a 30\" Haier, verify the model number, you may have a GE Appliances product (GE is the full-size US line; both brands under same Haier Group parent but separate product lineups). Model number starts with GE prefix conventions on GE products vs Haier-specific model-number patterns on Haier products."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Haier parts easy to get in LA?",
    a: "Parts availability is decent on current + recent Haier units (2016+, post-GE-acquisition era when Haier Group invested in US distribution expansion). Haier Group operates US parts distribution that expanded post-2016 with sibling-brand access to GE Appliances + Fisher &amp; Paykel + Casarte + AQUA logistics. Common Haier oven parts (bake elements, thermal sensors, door hinges, gas igniters on gas models) typically arrive 3-5 days to LA authorized service. Specialty items (Wi-Fi modules, specific generation control boards, compact-format glass + door assembly) may run 5-10 day lead. Pre-2016 Haier units (imported before US distribution expansion) sometimes require aftermarket cross-reference, parts availability varies by specific generation. At diagnostic we identify generation + realistic parts-lead-time expectation before committing a repair timeline."
  },
  {
    q: "What Haier appliance categories do you service?",
    a: "Our Haier service covers the current US lineup: <b>24\" compact built-in ovens + ranges</b> (the core Haier US positioning), <b>24\" compact refrigerators</b> (top-freezer + bottom-freezer formats for urban apartments), <b>24\" compact dishwashers</b> (integrated-style + freestanding), <b>compact + stackable laundry</b> (Haier-branded washer + dryer), and <b>countertop + over-the-range microwaves</b> in compact formats. Specific oven coverage at <a href='/brands/haier-oven-repair/'>Haier oven repair</a>. Refrigerator coverage at <a href='/brands/haier-refrigerator-repair/'>Haier refrigerator repair</a>. We don't service Casarte or AQUA (Haier Group sibling brands sold primarily in Asian markets, not the US), different product lines, different parts chains."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Haier Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Organization", "@id": canonical + "#brand",
    "name": "Haier", "url": canonical, "description": "Chinese Qingdao-headquartered appliance brand since 1984. Acquired GE Appliances in 2016 (both operate as distinct US brand lineups). US-market Haier focuses 24\" compact appliances for urban apartments + lofts + small kitchens. Haier Smart Home app (distinct from GE SmartHQ)."
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Haier", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Haier service? Same-day across LA:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Haier</div>
    <h1>Haier Appliance Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Haier is the Chinese Qingdao-headquartered appliance brand (Haier Group since 1984) whose US market positioning centers on <b>24\" compact appliances for urban apartments, lofts, and small-kitchen households</b>. Haier Group acquired GE Appliances in 2016, but the two brands operate as distinct US product lineups, GE Appliances covers full-size mainstream (30\" ranges, 30-36\" refrigerators, full-size laundry); Haier covers 24\" compact. Our LA Haier service concentrates in <b>DTLA lofts, West Hollywood high-rise condos, Koreatown 1930s apartment buildings, Silver Lake + Hollywood hills-side small kitchens, Santa Monica beach-town bungalows, and Beverly Hills guest-house kitchens</b>, the neighborhoods + installations where full-size US appliances don't fit the kitchen footprint. Haier Smart Home app service + Wi-Fi module diagnostics + 24\" compact parts-chain sourcing are the Haier-specific skill areas. Same-day dispatch. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Haier ≠ GE despite shared parent</b>, distinct US product lineups</li>
      <li><b>24\" compact specialization</b>, urban apartments + lofts + small kitchens</li>
      <li><b>Haier Smart Home app</b>, not GE SmartHQ (distinct ecosystems)</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Haier in LA, Chinese parent, US compact positioning, urban apartment concentration</h2>
    <p>Haier's US positioning is easy to misread because of the 2016 GE Appliances acquisition. Assumption: "Haier owns GE, so Haier and GE are the same brand now." Reality: <b>Haier and GE Appliances operate as distinct US product lineups</b>. GE Appliances continues full-size mainstream at its established $800-$2,500 price tier; Haier continues 24\" compact specialization at $500-$1,500 price tier. Both brands contribute to Haier Group's broader portfolio, but US buyers choose between them for different kitchen needs, not as substitutes.</p>
    <p>Our LA Haier service concentration reflects the compact-kitchen use case. DTLA + Arts District lofts built post-2010 with modernist small kitchens that specified 24\" compact appliances at design; West Hollywood high-rise condos from the same era; Koreatown + Westlake 1920s-1940s apartment buildings where kitchen cutouts predate 30\" US appliance standardization; Silver Lake + Echo Park bungalows with small galley kitchens; Santa Monica + Venice beach cottages. Each represents a kitchen footprint that fits Haier better than mainstream US brands.</p>
    <p>What's changed since Haier Group's 2016 GE acquisition: US parts distribution for Haier expanded significantly, common 24\" compact parts (bake elements, thermal sensors, gas igniters, door hinges) now arrive 3-5 days to LA authorized service via improved sibling-brand logistics (GE Appliances + Fisher &amp; Paykel + Casarte + AQUA share Haier Group distribution efficiency). Pre-2016 Haier units sometimes require aftermarket cross-reference for specialty parts; post-2016 Haier has a real US parts-chain behind it.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Haier appliance categories we service in LA</h2>
    <div class="cat-grid-simple">
      <a href="/brands/haier-oven-repair/" class="cat-card-link">
        <h3>Haier oven repair →</h3>
        <p>24\" compact built-in ovens + range-integrated. 52 imp GSC demand. Urban-apartment concentration.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/brands/haier-refrigerator-repair/" class="cat-card-link">
        <h3>Haier refrigerator repair →</h3>
        <p>24\" compact refrigerators (top-freezer + bottom-freezer). Already deployed.</p>
      </a>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Haier 24\" range repair</h3>
        <p>Compact gas + electric ranges with integrated oven. ADU + apartment + loft concentration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Haier 24\" dishwasher repair</h3>
        <p>Compact integrated-style + freestanding dishwashers. Urban-kitchen small-footprint fit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Haier compact laundry</h3>
        <p>Stackable + all-in-one washer/dryer combination units for apartments without dedicated laundry hookup.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Haier microwave + small appliances</h3>
        <p>Countertop + over-the-range compact microwaves. Magnetron + door switch + control diagnostic.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>LA neighborhoods, where our Haier service concentrates</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>DTLA + Arts District lofts</h4><p>Downtown LA · Arts District · South Park · Historic Core · Little Tokyo · Fashion District, modernist small-kitchen lofts</p></div>
      <div><h4>West Hollywood high-rise</h4><p><a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a> · Sunset Strip · Doheny · Norma Triangle, luxury condo compact kitchens</p></div>
      <div><h4>Koreatown + Westlake apartments</h4><p>Koreatown · Westlake · MacArthur Park · Wilshire Center, 1920s-1940s apartment stock</p></div>
      <div><h4>Silver Lake + Echo Park</h4><p>Silver Lake · Echo Park · Los Feliz · Atwater, bungalow + cottage small kitchens</p></div>
      <div><h4>Santa Monica + Venice beach</h4><p><a href="/santa-monica/">Santa Monica</a> · Venice · Ocean Park · Main Street, beach-town cottage kitchens</p></div>
      <div><h4>Beverly Hills guest-houses + ADU</h4><p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air guest-houses · ADU conversions citywide</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Haier and compact-appliance pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/haier-oven-repair/">Haier oven repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/haier-refrigerator-repair/">Haier refrigerator repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/ge/">GE hub (full-size US sibling under Haier Group) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/fisher-paykel/">Fisher &amp; Paykel hub (NZ premium Haier Group sibling) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/magic-chef/">Magic Chef hub (compact peer) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/oven-repair/">Oven repair service hub →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Haier appliance repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Haier service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--black); }
  h4 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .cat-grid-simple { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .cat-card-link, .cat-card-link-static { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; display: block; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: all .2s; }
  .cat-card-link:hover { border-color: var(--red); transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .cat-card-link h3, .cat-card-link-static h3 { color: var(--black); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .cat-card-link p, .cat-card-link-static p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.94rem; margin: 0; }
  .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
  .area-grid > div { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; } .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .related-links a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; } .related-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } h2 { font-size: 1.45rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
